Pre-requisite to run the program:
--------------------------------

1. You need to have java installed on your system. I recommend using java 7.

Required classpath files:
-------------------------

1. All java files are compiled into amortization.jar. You can just reference
   this jar in classpath to launch the program.

Running amortization schedule prgoram:
--------------------------------------

java -cp amortization.jar amortization.AmortizationSchedule

Input to file:
--------------

Once the program is launched, it will ask for following input:

1. Amount to be borrowed in dollars as integer.
2. Annual percentage rate as floating number.
3. Term period in number of months.

Output:
-------

It will output amortization schedule if all input parameter is correct. Else,
it will throw a validation error which needs ot be corrected.